GO analysis

This is an alternative approach to using the fgsea method (see “04_fgsea.Rmd”) which is better suited to compare it with other findings of Imke Lemmer.

# loading DESeq2 results (`res.gastroc`, and `res.soleus`):
load("./data/Robjects/02_DDS.RData")

# loading annotation data for entrez ids (GRCm39):
load("./data/Robjects/03_annot.RData")

used genome: Biomart Database (GRCm39)

clusterProfiler: enrichGO

performGO_dotplot <- function(entrez_ids, plot_name, pCutoff = params$pCutoff) {
  result_GO <- enrichGO(
    entrez_ids,
    OrgDb =  "org.Mm.eg.db",
    ont = "BP",
    pAdjustMethod = "BH",
    pvalueCutoff = pCutoff,
    readable = T
  )
  
  # plot:
  p <- dotplot(result_GO, showCategory = 15) +
    scale_color_gradient(
      low = "red",
      high = "blue",
      labels = function(x)
        format(x, digits = 2)
    )
  ggsave(
    filename = file.path(
      plot.dir,
      paste0("05_enrichGO_dotplot_", plot_name, ".svg")
    ),
    plot = p
  )
  return(p)
}

all gastroc

ids <- res.gastroc %>%
  data.frame() %>% 
  filter(padj < params$pCutoff, baseMean > 100) %>% 
  merge(annot[,c("GeneID", "entrezgene_id")], by.x = 0, by.y = "GeneID") %>% 
  pull("entrezgene_id")

performGO_dotplot(entrez_ids = ids, "gastroc_general")
